Risk 360 Platform
Fundamental problems with management of operational risks brings following factors into the play. viz. framing,
cognitive bias and groupthink. Contrary to other risks operational risks are usually not willingly incurred nor are
they revenue driven. Also, operational risk is not diversifiable i.e., if people, systems, and processes remain
imperfect, operational risk cannot be fully eliminated.
The solution is targeted at the loan account maintenance team which can take preventive measures if the asset
quality indicator drops beyond certain level. Risk underwriting team will also be able to use the system for ad
hoc credit assessment. The system provides dashboard for the users based on the role and automated periodic
alerts and reports. Portfolio level dashboard would be available for top management. The dashboard would allow
drill-down based on asset categories, geography, and other parameters.
The proposed solution leverages analytics to reduce the information overload on the team and provide them
with actionable insights. The platform would collect information from publicly available sources.

CN;Private&Confidential aashutosh
The platform will help the banks manage risk from three dimensions:
 Reducing the Probability of Default by creating early warning list
 Reducing Loss Given Default (LGD) by maximizing collateralization for sectors or customers on early
warning list
 Reducing Exposure at Default (EAD) by early interventions, mandatory actions and reducing exposure to
high-risk geographies, industrial clusters
Proposed solution will have two variants SCREEN360 for Due-diligence, Screening and Assessment and
EWS360 for Ongoing-monitoring.
SCREEN360
The purpose of this variant is to avoid risk knowledge gap with better due diligence. A superficial evaluation is
not sufficient to proactively assess and mitigate risk. This variant will focus on screening clients and customers
against PEPs, 100+ sanction, OFAC, AML/CFT and defaulter list, and internal lists as part of KYC process. This
will be especially useful for Trade Finance desk which handles Letter of Credit / Bank Guarantees from overseas
entities.
This variant will vet potential customers beyond financial stress scores to capture an accurate picture of risk.
This information may include:
 Financial, legal, and business information on private, public, and international entities
 Company profiles and information beyond typical self-reported data
 Negative news, employee, and customer views
 Compliance and litigation history
EWS360
Currently, the banks monitoring is done through information submitted by the customer in the form of stock
statement, monthly select operational data (MSOD), quarterly information system (QIS), half yearly operating
statement and credit audit report. The credit audit is conducted at two places one at branch level, another at
central level. Monitoring in the form of payment to suppliers and receipt from customers is also done by the
operations team. However, external events like accident / fire at factory, change in management, death of the
promoter/partner, labour strike, customer and employee discontent, unfavorable industrial policy changes etc.
are not monitored.
This variant will uncover hidden risks using open-web information sourced from news, business, legal, and social
media. Early-warning tracking of small changes in customers’ situations can make a big impact on the bottom
line of banks. Better credit monitoring can be one of the main ways that capital-strapped banks can improve
their business model. This product variant monitors open-web sources for early warning indicators and effectively
reduces net exposure at default. Armed with always up-to-date perspective and automated alerts, banks will get
real-time insights and reduce vulnerability.

Solution Expectations
The purpose of the solution is to create efficient monitoring mechanism is automated, streamlined, and
consistent across the asset-class. The solution will provide required drill down of the information so that the
source can be tracked, if needed thereby creating audit trail of the generated report.
Core Triggers
and
Early Warning
System
 Integration with internal Technical Triggers like overdrawing, delayed payment
 Manual user triggers based on operational data
 External data triggers
 Segregating accounts into different watchlist categories based on pre-defined risk
buckets
Management of
Watchlist
 Movement from one bucket to another
 Recoding of Actions and List of Recommended Actions for user
 Reporting of actions taken and control-return for success/failure of action
Back-testing
 Ability to back-test and categorise the accounts based on historical crawled records
(say, two years)
The solution should have a workflow management system which will address following automations and
reporting
 Flag ratio - % of customers flagged by the system and transferred to watch list
 Exceptions – How many of the restructuring or SMA (Special Mention Accounts) are not there in the
watchlist.
 Selectivity – How many substandard accounts as opposed to regular accounts are flagged by the system
 Time – What is the average time of default after system triggers an alert
CN;Private&Confidential aashutosh
Following items should be taken into consideration while designing the system
 The watch-list should have several categories to be managed based on different-buckets of risk severity.
 Tracking of mitigating actions taken and recording of the same.
 Knowledge management to ensure that lessons learned from successful mitigation are automatically
applied to new watch-list assets.
SCREEN360 will take input using multiple options – batch, integration with existing system and manual search
by a user or an API.
EWS360 will either be integrated with the system or the monitoring database will be updated through an API.
The system will regularly monitor the data sources based on applicable frequency. e.g.
